---
description: Run the full DoD checklist and prepare for deployment
agent: build
---

Run the Definition of Done validation:

```bash
echo "=== DoD Check ==="

# DoD-1: No debug code
grep -rn "fmt\.Println\|console\.log\|debugger;" \
  --include="*.go" --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx" \
  --exclude-dir={node_modules,.next,dist} \
  --exclude="*_test*" . 2>/dev/null \
  && echo "FAIL: debug code found" || echo "PASS: no debug code"

# DoD-2: No hardcoded secrets
grep -rn 'password\s*=\s*["'"'"']\|api_key\s*=\s*["'"'"']' \
  --include="*.go" --include="*.ts" --include="*.py" . 2>/dev/null \
  && echo "FAIL: hardcoded secrets found" || echo "PASS: no hardcoded secrets"

# DoD-3: No destructive migrations
grep -rn "DROP COLUMN\|RENAME COLUMN\|DROP TABLE" \
  --include="*.sql" . 2>/dev/null \
  && echo "FAIL: destructive migration found" || echo "PASS: migrations safe"

# DoD-4: Build passes
{{ if eq .Framework "encore" }}encore build{{ else if eq .Framework "fastapi" }}python -m py_compile $(find src -name '*.py'){{ else if eq .Framework "axum" }}cargo build --release{{ else if eq .Frontend "nextjs" }}npm run build{{ else }}go build ./...{{ end }} 2>&1 && echo "PASS: build passes" || echo "FAIL: build failed"
```

Report results. If all pass, provide deployment checklist.
